On 22-Sep-04, at 7:51 PM, Michael Knight wrote:

Then I tested the pump again be running a jumper from the + side of the 
battery straight to the pump. BINGO! It was so nice to here that light 
swirling sound. I didn't quit though, I put a switch in the line to act 
as a breaker for the pump, connected the power again, key on, with 
remote starter in hand. She turned over and over and over then 
puff......puff.....puff...puff..puff. puff.......twisted the dizzy. 
Vvvrrrooooommm! Like clock work I hit the timing close and she was 
running. WOOOOOOOOOOOHOOOOOOOOOOO!

Now I just need to get that relay and work out the kinks, doesn't idle 
well as of yet. But beyond idle she sounds great.

